race.comment: MR PLAYTIME (3) resumes here but the form he showed when last in work was good enough for a race of this calibre. Revved up for this with a recent trial win and only needs some luck navigating from the sticky draw to be playing a major role in the finish. MISHANI HERCULES (2) is unlucky to still be a maiden finishing runner-up at his past couple over this sprint trip. Top-three aspirations. Former NSW galloper EXCESS CAPITAL (7) is having her first run for the new stable but should find this easier than what she faced down south. Respect any market confidence. AIR CONTROL (1) makes some appeal from the favourable draw at odds.
